"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1928033-paris-olympic-boxing-rules-scoring\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The2024 Paris Olympicshas kicked off and today marks the beginning of theboxingevents.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 88, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 15, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999977894731, \"rank\": 2.21050323357688e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the beginning\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 66}, {\"ngram\": \"theboxingevents\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 85}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport, which is almost as old as human civilization itself, was part of the ancient Olympic Games, first appearing in 688 BC, and has been a mainstay in the modern Olympics since 1920.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 215, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.7288259706409581, \"rank\": 0.34388760395459406, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sport\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"human civilization\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 144}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 161}, {\"ngram\": \"the ancient Olympic Games\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 190}, {\"ngram\": \"a mainstay\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As one of the most popular and widespread sports of the 21st century, boxing is set to once again enthral Olympic audiences, with 13 events and 39 medals on offer in Paris.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999977894731, \"rank\": 2.21050323357688e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most popular and widespread sports\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 327}, {\"ngram\": \"the 21st century\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"boxing\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 355}, {\"ngram\": \"enthral Olympic audiences\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 402}, {\"ngram\": \"13 events\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"39 medals\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it's worth noting that boxing at the Games differs from professional circuit boxing.\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 503}, {\"ngram\": \"professional circuit boxing\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here,Express Sportdelves into these differences to provide all the necessary information for both boxing enthusiasts and casual viewers.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Here,Express Sportdelves\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 571}, {\"ngram\": \"these differences\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"all the necessary information\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"both boxing enthusiasts\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"casual viewers\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic boxing matches for both men and women consist of three rounds of three minutes each.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic boxing matches\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"both men\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"three rounds\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"three minutes\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a one-minute break between each round.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a one-minute break\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 805}, {\"ngram\": \"each round\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rationale behind such short-round fights is to safeguard the athletes, many of whom will have to compete multiple times throughout the Games.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rationale\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"such short-round fights\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the Rio 2016 Olympics, the scoring system in Olympic boxing mirrored that of amateur boxing, which is solely based on the number of hits landed.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9766159018048107, \"rank\": 0.02394400721116008, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3117564605966653e-16, \"text\": \"2016 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the scoring system\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic boxing\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1039}, {\"ngram\": \"amateur boxing\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"hits\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, eight years ago, following a rule change allowing professional boxers to participate in the Games for the first time, the 10-point-must system was introduced.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rule change\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"professional boxers\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10-point-must system\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For those unfamiliar, professional boxing utilises the 10-point-must system, where judges score each round individually on a 10-point scale, with the round's victor receiving 10 points.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"professional boxing\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10-point-must system\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"judges\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"each round\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"a 10-point scale\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"the round's victor\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"10 points\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, unlike in professional boxing, Olympic boxing employs five judges instead of three.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"professional boxing\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic boxing\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"five judges\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of every round, these judges determine a winner based on the number of hits landed and award that individual 10 points.\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"every round\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"these judges\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"a 